# Mission Control: Visual Agent Task Manager

Kanban board for managing agent tasks through gstack's skill pipeline. Cards bind to durable OpenClaw sessions, support inline human replies, and can carry image attachments so agents can see mockups/screenshots during stage runs.

## Quick Start

```bash
$K start          # Start Mission Control server
$K open           # Open board in browser
$K show           # Print board state to terminal
$K add "title"    # Add card to backlog
$K move <id> <col> # Move card to column
$K process        # List pending cards for execution
$K stop           # Stop server
```

## Column Pipeline

| Column | Skill | Purpose |
|--------|-------|---------|
| Backlog | — | New tasks |
| Office Hours | /office-hours | Reframe the problem |
| CEO Review | /plan-ceo-review | Find the 10-star product |
| Eng Review | /plan-eng-review | Lock architecture |
| Design Review | /plan-design-review | Rate design dimensions |
| Design | /design-consultation | Build design system |
| Implementation | — | Agent writes code |
| Code Review | /review | Pre-landing review |
| Debug | /debug | Root-cause investigation |
| QA | /qa | Browser-based testing |
| Ship | /ship | Test, review, push, PR |
| Docs | /document-release | Update docs |
| Retro | /retro | Weekly retrospective |
| Done | — | Completed |

## Processing Pending Cards

When `$K process` shows pending cards, execute the corresponding skill for each:

1. Read the card's title and description for context
2. Run the skill listed in `skillTriggered`
3. Update the card status when done: `$K move <id> <next-column>`

## Environment Variables

- `MISSION_CONTROL_PASSWORD` — Password for web UI auth (optional, no auth if unset)
- `MC_OPENCLAW_AGENT_ID` — Agent id whose durable session store cards bind to (default: `main`)
- `MC_AGENT_TIMEOUT_SECONDS` — Timeout for each `openclaw agent` stage run (default: `1800`)
- `MC_BASE_PATH` — Optional URL prefix when Mission Control is served behind a subpath like `/missioncontrol`
- `MC_PORT` — Override server port (default: random)
